{"type":"message","id":"48896673","parentId":"05f07afd","timestamp":"2026-04-25T07:41:28.236Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the desktop app structure is there but `dist/backend/` doesn't exist yet, meaning the backend hasn't been built yet. The user wants a standalone desktop version. \n\nLet me think about what this means:\n1. The `daily_stock_analysis` repo code is already integrated into their quant investment system\n2. They want a separate desktop version\n\nFor a desktop version, we need:\n1. The FastAPI backend (Python) + Electron frontend\n2. The backend needs to be packaged with PyInstaller\n3. The Electron app needs to be built\n\nSince the user is on macOS (based on the runtime info showing Darwin), we'd be building for macOS. \n\nLooking at the architecture, the Electron app actually expects a backend executable in `dist/backend/` to run the packaged Python API server. So I need to figure out whether they want me to build a complete working desktop app from scratch, or just set up the project structure and configuration files so they can build it themselves.\n\nLet me check what the build process actually requires - it looks like they need Node.js and npm for the Electron app, Python with pip and PyInstaller for the backend, and the Electron builder package. Since they're on macOS (Darwin ARM64), I'd need to build for macOS specifically rather than Windows. The most straightforward approach would be to first ensure the backend can be packaged as a standalone executable, then configure the Electron app to reference it properly, and finally run the build to generate the macOS app.\n","thinkingSignature":"f90234f25620919f0198761c6e5902af746c24c3d5fdc8d258d4d2a775762799"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n桌面版需要 PyInstaller 打包 Python 后端 + Electron 打包前端。让我先看一下现有的构建脚本和环境。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7mgceq7aqg66_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/scripts/ | grep -E \"desktop|build|pyinstaller\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":134,"output":382,"cacheRead":60128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60644,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777102880807,"responseId":"063ba321da592daf478d44f574b46fae"}}
{"type":"message","id":"62a9457b","parentId":"48896673","timestamp":"2026-04-25T07:41:28.289Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7mgceq7aqg66_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"build-all-macos.sh\nbuild-all.ps1\nbuild-backend-macos.sh\nbuild-backend.ps1\nbuild-desktop-macos.sh\nbuild-desktop.ps1\nrun-desktop.ps1"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"build-all-macos.sh\nbuild-all.ps1\nbuild-backend-macos.sh\nbuild-backend.ps1\nbuild-desktop-macos.sh\nbuild-desktop.ps1\nrun-desktop.ps1","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777102888278}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4d77fd1","parentId":"62a9457b","timestamp":"2026-04-25T07:41:48.647Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me give the user a clear plan:\n\nFor a standalone desktop version, they need:\n\n1. **Backend**: Python app with PyInstaller\n2. **Frontend**: React UI built with Vite\n3. **Electron shell**: The desktop wrapper\n\nSince the repo already has `daily_stock_analysis` merged into their quant system, they want a **separate, self-contained desktop version** with its own:\n- `.env` configuration\n- Data directory\n- Logs\n\nThe key steps for macOS desktop build:\n1. Build the React UI (`apps/dsa-web`)\n2. Build the Python backend with PyInstaller\n\n\n3. Package everything with Electron\n\nI should check if there's an existing `.env.example` to understand what environment variables need to be configured, and verify whether the backend build script is ready to use on macOS.\n","thinkingSignature":"0f42bf5546d7d04f7d1912e7b2c9696f50379e0fe7a56ce2ef6684299b61ce3a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1jig69se0axs_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/scripts/build-desktop-macos.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1jig69se0axs_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/.env.example 2>/dev/null && echo \"exists\" || echo \"not found\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111,"output":278,"cacheRead":60256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777102888289,"responseId":"063ba328e63fa12eef3ffee6895f4c8f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b36d7a80","parentId":"a4d77fd1","timestamp":"2026-04-25T07:41:48.747Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1jig69se0axs_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\nROOT_DIR=\"$(cd \"${SCRIPT_DIR}/..\" && pwd)\"\n\nexport CSC_IDENTITY_AUTO_DISCOVERY=\"false\"\nexport ELECTRON_BUILDER_CACHE=\"${ROOT_DIR}/.electron-builder-cache\"\n\necho \"Building Electron desktop app (macOS)...\"\n\nif [[ ! -d \"${ROOT_DIR}/dist/backend/stock_analysis\" ]]; then\n  echo \"Backend artifact not found: ${ROOT_DIR}/dist/backend/stock_analysis\"\n  echo \"Run scripts/build-backend-macos.sh first.\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\npushd \"${ROOT_DIR}/apps/dsa-desktop\" >/dev/null\nif [[ ! -d node_modules ]]; then\n  npm install\nfi\n\nif compgen -G \"dist/mac*\" >/dev/null; then\n  echo \"Cleaning dist/mac*...\"\n  rm -rf dist/mac*\nfi\n\nMAC_ARCH=\"${DSA_MAC_ARCH:-}\"\nARCH_ARGS=()\nif [[ -n \"${MAC_ARCH}\" ]]; then\n  case \"${MAC_ARCH}\" in\n    x64|arm64)\n      ARCH_ARGS+=(\"--${MAC_ARCH}\")\n      ;;\n    *)\n      echo \"Unsupported DSA_MAC_ARCH: ${MAC_ARCH}. Use x64 or arm64.\"\n      exit 1\n      ;;\n  esac\nfi\n\necho \"Building macOS target arch: ${MAC_ARCH:-default}\"\nif [[ ${#ARCH_ARGS[@]} -gt 0 ]]; then\n  npx electron-builder --mac dmg \"${ARCH_ARGS[@]}\"\nelse\n  npx electron-builder --mac dmg\nfi\npopd >/dev/null\n\necho \"Desktop build completed.\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777102908738}}
