{"type":"message","id":"32b5efac","parentId":"389dfe7a","timestamp":"2026-04-25T07:43:00.873Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to configure a standalone desktop version of the daily_stock_analysis repo. Looking at the docs:\n\n1. The project already has a `dsa-desktop` (Electron + React UI) app\n2. The `build-desktop-macos.sh` script requires building the backend first with `build-backend-macos.sh`\n3. The backend artifact is expected at `dist/backend/stock_analysis`\n4. Both `apps/dsa-web` and `apps/dsa-desktop` don't have `node_modules` installed\n\nThe user said \"这个仓库已经融合在我的量化投资系统了，但是我还想单独配置一个桌面版的\" - meaning it's already integrated into their quant system, but they want a separate desktop deployment.\n\n\nI'm realizing the setup path matters here. The original project lives at `/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/`, but since they're already running this as part of their quant system with its own `.env`, workspace, and Python environment, they'd probably want the desktop version set up in a separate directory to avoid conflicts. The challenge is that the build scripts reference hardcoded paths back to the original repo location, so I need to figure out whether they want the desktop app to remain integrated with the existing quant system or run independently. I need to identify what's actually missing for a standalone macOS desktop build—the backend binary, node_modules for both web and desktop apps, and checking whether electron-builder can even run on this machine since Electron isn't installed.\n","thinkingSignature":"0dad8c958d8225dc8833b53f5b61c67eb5948827fef3a8f827435c45d63e221a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hbq864x9eqdv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"brew list --cask 2>/dev/null | grep -i electron; brew list 2>/dev/null | grep -i electron; which brew"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8