{"type":"message","id":"bb268493","parentId":"17def1f0","timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:13:34.176Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The .env file is there but there's no `data/` or `logs/` directory. Also, the app needs a backend to be running. The backend in the packaged app is the `stock_analysis` binary. Let me check if the backend binary is properly packaged.\n\nWait, looking at the main.js code again:\n```javascript\nfunction resolveBackendPath() {\n  if (app.isPackaged) {\n    const backendDir = path.join(process.resourcesPath, 'backend');\n    const exeName = isWindows ? 'stock_analysis.exe' : 'stock_analysis';\n    const oneDirPath = path.join(backendDir, 'stock_analysis', exeName);\n    if (fs.existsSync(oneDirPath)) {\n      return oneDirPath;\n    }\n    return path.join(backendDir, exeName);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\nWhen not packaged (`app.isPackaged` is false), it falls through to the else branch which uses `python` + `main.py`. But the desktop app is packaged (.app), so it should look for the binary in `process.resourcesPath/backend/`.\n\nWait, but we built the backend into `dist/backend/stock_analysis/` which gets copied to `apps/dsa-desktop/dist/mac-arm64/`... Let me check if the .app bundle has the right structure.\n\nActually, looking at the build output again, the DMG was created at:\n```\ndist/Daily Stock Analysis-3.12.0-arm64.dmg\n```\n\nThis DMG contains the `mac-arm64/Daily Stock Analysis.app` bundle. But did electron-builder copy the backend binary into the app bundle?\n\nLet me check the `apps/dsa-desktop/dist/mac-arm64/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/Resources/` directory.","thinkingSignature":"4e8539fc868df7da0cde52cb115d89f7a576fc7cc5cbd84ce3136dd33d22ba27"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0zfc55yhfz72_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/apps/dsa-desktop/dist/mac-arm64/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/Resou