{"type":"message","id":"2dcb761a","parentId":"fe4554ec","timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:15:31.365Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backend is missing the `api` module. This means the PyInstaller build didn't include all necessary modules. The `api/` directory exists in the source but wasn't included in the hidden imports during PyInstaller.\n\nLooking at the build-backend script, the hidden imports include `api`, `api.app`, `api.deps`, etc. - but the issue is that when running from the packaged app, the `api` module can't be found.\n\nWait, the health check passed (curl returned something), so the server IS running on port 8099. The error happened AFTER the health check succeeded - it's an Exception in a thread that's not the main server thread.\n \nThe issue is that the FastAPI app is trying to import the `api` module but failing because it's not bundled in the PyInstaller executable, even though `api/` is in the source directory. This could be a Python 3.14 compatibility issue with the `api.v1` routing or possibly a missing module in the packaged dependencies.\n\nLooking at the logs, the health endpoint actually returned a 307 redirect, not a 200, which means the health check technically passed but the redirect suggests the API is misconfigured. The module import error happens after the initial server startup succeeds, so the server is running but then fails when trying to load the API routes.\n\nThe issue is that PyInstaller only detects imports that are explicitly called in the code at runtime. Since `api.v1.router` and other API modules are only imported when FastAPI loads the app, PyInstaller doesn't know to bundle them, especially with the `--onedir` format which uses runtime hooks rather than full static analysis. The hidden imports in the build script should theoretically handle this, but something in the runtime import chain is still missing. Looking at the stack trace more carefully, the module import failure is happening inside uvicorn's serve function during server initialization, which suggests the issue is with how uvicorn is loading the application module rather than the earlier health check endpoint.\n\nThe fact that curl successfully hit the health endpoint but then the server crashed with a module import error indicates the server started on 8099 but then failed when trying to load the router. I should check the main.py startup code to understand what's happening between the health endpoint and the router loading. The stack trace shows the import error occurs in uvicorn's `load` method when it tries to import the FastAPI app, which means the server starts but crashes when the router module can't be found. I should check what's happening at the health endpoint and whether uvicorn is finding the correct working directory at runtime. Let me review the main.js to see if the path is resolving correctly.\n\nActually, I think I found it - the backend is likely starting in the wrong working directory. The main.js sets `launchCwd = path.dirname(backendPath)` which means the backend runs from `/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/Resources/backend/stock_analysis/`, but the application code probably expects to be run from the repository root or a different location. The logs show the issue clearly - the backend started successfully and the server was listening, but then crashed when trying to load the API module. This happened because curl got a response before the crash, so the health check passed initially but then the app failed when actually loading the API routes.\n\nThe backend binary was built with `pip install -r requirements.txt` but the user's system Python is 3.14, which might have compatibility issues with some packages. I should check if there's a virtual environment with the right dependencies that can be bundled with the app, or guide the user through setting up their environment properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"ff9b7cf4fd0779eebc016419f0692c02e914213ce6ff526f25e2bdd15fb43eac"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n后端打包时遗漏了 `api` 模块。我来重新构建：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2h0kcz0j4xoh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/dist/backend/stock_analysis/_internal/ | grep api"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1206,"output":808,"cacheRead":90912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92926,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777104899444,"responseId":"063bab05b063b063f524165eda2464e6"}}
