{"type":"message","id":"f0fee67b","parentId":"f49e6fd7","timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:15:42.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backend binary was built without the `api` module. This is likely because during the PyInstaller build, we didn't include all the hidden imports for the API module. Looking at the build script, it has many `--hidden-import` entries for the API module, but when I ran the build manually, I didn't include those flags.\n\nThe issue is that the `api/` directory exists in the source code, but the PyInstaller binary doesn't have it bundled. I need to rebuild with the proper `--hidden-import` flags.\n\nLet me rebuild properly, including all the hidden imports from the build script.","thinkingSignature":"dafd269c55c675de45b7c5873298903c99fe52265d764d8a2b36fbc56f3300a5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n问题是 PyInstaller 打包时漏掉了 `api` 模块，需要重新构建后端。正在重建...\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q68b810lwp74_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis && python3 -m PyInstaller --name stock_analysis --onedir --noconfirm --noconsole --add-data \"static:static\" --collect-data litellm --collect-data tiktoken \\\n  --hidden-import=multipart --hidden-import=multipart.multipart \\\n  --hidden-import=json_repair --hidden-import=tiktoken --hidden-import=tiktoken_ext --hidden-import=tiktoken_ext.openai_public \\\n  --hidden-import=api --hidden-import=api.app --hidden-import=api.deps \\\n  --hidden-import=api.v1 --hidden-import=api.v1.router --hidden-import=api.v1.endpoints \\\n  --hidden-import=api.v1.endpoints.analysis --hidden-import=api.v1.endpoints.history \\\n  --hidden-import=api.v1.endpoints.stocks --hidden-import=api.v1.endpoints.health \\\n  --hidden-import=api.v1.schemas --hidden-import=api.v1.schemas.analysis --hidden-import=api.v1.schemas.history \\\n  --hidden-import=api.v1.schemas.stocks --hidden-import=api.v1.schemas.common \\\n  --hidden-im