{"type":"message","id":"8d94be98","parentId":"6598963f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:29:20.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The desktop app writes logs to the `logs/desktop.log` relative to the app directory (which is `~/Library/Application Support/Daily Stock Analysis/`). But that directory doesn't have a `logs` subdirectory. Looking at the main.js code:\n\n```javascript\nfunction initLogging() {\n  const appDir = app.isPackaged ? path.dirname(app.getPath('exe')) : app.getPath('userData');\n  logFilePath = path.join(appDir, 'logs', 'desktop.log');\n```\n\nSo for the packaged app, logs go to `path.dirname(app.getPath('exe'))/logs/desktop.log`, which would be `/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/MacOS/logs/desktop.log`... wait, no. `path.dirname(app.getPath('exe'))` would be `/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/MacOS/`... no wait, `app.getPath('exe')` is the path to the executable `/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/MacOS/Daily Stock Analysis`, so `path.dirname()` of that is `/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/MacOS/`. \n\nThen `logs/desktop.log` would be at `/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/MacOS/logs/desktop.log`. Let me check if that file exists.","thinkingSignature":"c140ffed7731c15566c843fa20b6237baa4e0cd8850b62aee6626fb7cdf9b3ee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bwx8mnbc2fg1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat \"/Applications/Daily Stock Analysis.app/Contents/MacOS/logs/desktop.log\" 2>/dev/null | tail -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":151,"output":319,"cacheRead":100800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101270,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777105752757,"responseId":"063bae593be2733ba00dd55e22f89eaa"}}
