{"type":"message","id":"172330ba","parentId":"11cdb81b","timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:38:49.027Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the base class's `_record_error` takes 2 args (self, key), and the MiniMaxSearchProvider's `_record_error` overrides it with 2 args (self, key) - exactly matching. But there's a call to `_record_error(api_key, str(e))` with 3 args (self, api_key, error_message).\n\nThe issue is in line 277: `self._record_error(api_key, str(e))` but MiniMax's `_record_error` only takes 2 args (self, key). This is a call site issue.\n\nLooking at line 272-277:\n```python\nself._record_error(api_key, response.error_message or \"\")\n\n\n```\nand\n```python\nself._record_error(api_key, str(e))\n```\n\nThese are calling `_record_error` with 3 args but the method only accepts 2. I need to check how the base class `BaseSearchProvider._record_error` is defined to understand the expected signature.","thinkingSignature":"042bde05535c4b48c25fa7619123d1d459b7c6fe3942d822662b88759f5dc6d4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hdcj86gwg1yw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":218,"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/src/search_service.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":303,"output":266,"cacheRead":105408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105977,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777106323249,"responseId":"063bb09344b032cb5f86e6a99db767fe"}}
