{"type":"message","id":"5249bba6","parentId":"912be2ee","timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:53:24.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user got an analysis result but it's basically useless - lots of \"N/A\" and \"待补充\" (to be filled in). This is because:\n\n1. The Ollama DeepSeek model isn't being used properly - it's running locally but might not be generating proper responses\n2. Or the search results are empty because MiniMax was disabled and other search sources might not be configured\n\nLet me think about what's happening:\n- The analysis ran and returned a result\n- But the LLM analysis part seems to have failed - lots of \"待补充\" and \"N/A\" fields\n- This means the AI model either didn't generate proper content or the data pipeline to the LLM failed\n\n\n- The backend is using Ollama locally, but the user might not have the Ollama server running, or the model could be failing to generate proper responses without Vision capabilities\n\nLooking at the specific failures, the search provider crashed when calling `_record_error()` with three arguments instead of two, which means the error handling broke the whole pipeline. I fixed the signature mismatch in the source, but the packaged build might still be shipping the old cached version since PyInstaller doesn't necessarily update everything cleanly.\n\nThe analysis completed despite this error, but the results are full of \"待补充\" (to be filled in) placeholders, which tells me the AI model either isn't configured correctly or the data sources feeding into it aren't working properly. The core issue is that the backend can't reach an AI model - whether that's because Ollama isn't running locally, the model isn't available, or the search API keys aren't set up to provide context.\n\nSince \"待补充\" means the AI didn't generate actual content, I need to verify if Ollama is actually running and accessible to the backend. The simplest approach would be to enable a cloud-based AI solution like Gemini that doesn't require local setup, or help the user get Ollama properly configured first.\n\nLooking at the config, we have both an Ollama endpoint and a MiniMax API key available. MiniMax would work for search functionality, but for the AI analysis component itself, we really need something like Gemini, Claude, or DeepSeek as a fallback since Ollama's models seem to struggle with structured financial analysis output.\n\nThe real issue is that even with Ollama configured, we're getting placeholder responses instead of actual analysis. Let me verify if Ollama is even running as a local server, and if not, we should switch to Gemini for both search and analysis since the user already has the API key.\n\nActually, looking at the logs more carefully - the analysis did complete, but the MiniMax search provider error is likely corrupting the data pipeline before it reaches the LLM. The \"待补充\" placeholders in the response suggest the LLM isn't receiving proper context. I should ask whether they want to stick with local Ollama for everything, or switch to a cloud-based AI solution for better reliability. which would be more reliable\n- Or we need to debug why Ollama is generating empty responses\n\nLet me ask the user what they want to do - stick with local Ollama or use a cloud model.","thinkingSignature":"5dd0a40a0f8d652b20d4f810030b05984c982ca4b576b03816040d5823a26e0c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n跑是跑起来了，但内容全是占位符（待补充、N/A），说明 AI 模型没有真正生成分析内容。\n\n本地 Ollama DeepSeek 在桌面打包这种离线环境里，对话式生成能力不稳定。**建议换成云端模型**，有几种方案：\n\n**方案1：Gemini（免费额度，推荐）**\n- 去 https://aistudio.google.com 申请免费 API Key\n- 填入 `GEMINI_API_KEY`，分析效果会稳定很多\n\n**方案2：继续用 MiniMax**\n- MiniMax 刚才只是 `_record_error` 的签名 bug 导致崩溃，修复后其实可以启用\n- 你的 Coding Plan API Key 可以用作搜索，但要确认是否支持 AI 对话（有些 Key 类型有限制）\n\n**方案3：配置 DeepSeek 云端 API**\n- 直接用 `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY`，比本地 Ollama 稳定\n\n你现在有其他云端 API Key 吗？或者要去申请一个 Gemini？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10856