{"type":"message","id":"2475e5bb","parentId":"3f4ae493","timestamp":"2026-04-25T09:59:54.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory flush - I need to store durable memories from this session to memory/2026-04-25.md. Let me check if it already exists and append new content.\n\nLet me recall what happened in this session:\n1. Continued setting up the desktop edition of daily_stock_analysis repo\n2. User provided MiniMax API key - stored in .env template\n3. User asked about local DeepSeek via Ollama - found deepseek-r1:14b model, configured for Ollama\n4. Rebuilt backend with correct PyInstaller hidden imports to fix \"api module not found\" error\n5. Fixed Feishu webhook configuration\n6. Debugged \"请求失败 - 返回空结果\" for stock 002920:\n   - First found pytdx/baostock connection failures\n   - User provided Tushare token and configured it\n   - Then found MiniMaxSearchProvider._record_error signature bug (3 args vs 2)\n   - Fixed by patching MiniMaxSearchProvider to accept error_message parameter\n   - Rebuilt backend with the fix\n7. Analysis ran but returned placeholder results (待补充, N/A)\n8. User agreed to try DeepSeek API (sk-1ad9c8ba7bf2413aa6f063a356ad6728)\n9. Updated .env with DEEPSEEK_API_KEY\n10. Later user asked about refreshing a dashboard at http://127.0.0.1:3847/cto_real_data_dashboard_latest.html\n\nKey memories to store:\n- Desktop DMG built successfully at size 485MB\n- Backend rebuild history (3 times) to fix packaging issues\n- Bug fixes applied (api module import, MiniMaxSearchProvider signature)\n- Configuration values (MiniMax key, Feishu webhook, DeepSeek key)\n- Current state: analysis runs but produces placeholder content; DeepSeek might fix this after restart","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_vXnr8MikkAwQUhyEzYuR2cJY","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent/memory/2026-04-25.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"